---
description: Supabase and database conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

Use Supabase/Postgres best practices.

Database rules:
- Prefer UUID primary keys.
- Use created_at and updated_at timestamps on major tables.
- Favor explicit foreign keys.
- Design for easy querying from Next.js frontend.
- Keep multilingual support structured and practical.
- Prepare for RLS later, but do not overcomplicate early schema design.
- Avoid polymorphic complexity unless clearly justified.
- When suggesting SQL, make it clean and runnable in Supabase.
- When changing schema, always explain migration impact on existing CCC features.